        "body": "<p>To test your code I used <code>C:/tmp/test.txt;<\/code> as your <code>args[0]<\/code>.  I fixed the issue by giving the output a filename to write to shown below:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Path dest = Paths.get(to);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>to<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Path dest = Paths.get(to, \"test2.txt\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>And it now successfully copied the file into that name, you can modify the filename however you want or add logic to change filename automatically.<\/p>\n",
